The operatives of the Department of State Services (DSS) have said the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu, refused to wear another clothes to appear in court. The DSS said this when Justice Binta Nyako queried why her order was flouted.  Nyako had ordered yesterday that the detained IPOB leader should not appear in court today in the same Fendi designers clothes he has been wearing since June last year when he was arrested. Kanu was on same clothes today, sparking a debate over why her order was flouted.



