I Don’t Want To See Nnamdi Kanu In These Clothes Again – Judge Orders Secret Police, DSS
0 Comments
1 Day Ago The prosecution team told the court that provision was made for a change of clothing for Kanu, but that the pro-Biafra secessionist rejected them on grounds that he preferred the designers Fendi he had on. When the matter was called up, the prosecution counsel, Mr Shuaibu Labaran, told the court that Kanu was the one that chose to wear his designer Fendi clothes. He said, “My lord, based on your order yesterday, we provided the defendant with a new orthopedic mattress, pillows and blankets. As for his appearance, he chose to wear this particular one because he said that it is designers.”



